Since `p = (ys', zs')`, we have `List.get p 0 = ys'` and `List.get p 1 = zs'`.
The definition of `splits (x :: xs)` is `([x], xs) :: (splits xs).map fun ⟨ys, zs⟩ => (x :: ys, zs)`.
The element `(x, List.get p 1)` (which is `(x, zs')`) is the head of the list `([x], xs)`.
